<Author>Joebella
<Content>Brilliant location and nice hotel My boyfriend and I travelled to Barcelona for the May bank holiday weekend as it was also my birthday. We had booked to stay in an apartment on the outskirts of Barcelona, however, on arrival we were absolutely disgusted by the apartment and only stayed the one night before finding Hotel Cortes.We had been wandering round Las Ramblas asking in a few hotels for prices, and this is just at the top of Ramblas, just off the main street down a quiet side street, this was the cheapest hotel we had been into and the reception even gave us the key and let us go have a look at the room before we booked it for the next 2 nights which we thought was really helpful. It cost us 拢130 for 2 nights and this included breakfast.I usually won't stay in anything less than a 4 star hotel, so was a bit aprehensive about stayng in a 2 star, but anything had to be better than the apartment we'd stayed in! The hotel actually surprised me! The rooms were basic and a bit tired (which is what you'd expect form a 2 star), but very clean and tidied daily, and they were also extremely spacious, as was the bathroom! I stayed ina 4 star hotel in Barcelona in January 2008 and had about half the room of this hotel The breakfast wasn't anything to write home about, just a selection of pastries and some oranage juice, but there was a gorgeous bakery a few doors down where we got some really nice stuff!The location is probably one of the best things about this hotel, it is right off Las Ramblas so you're in the heart of everything and is the perfect base for exploring. To be honest when staying in somewhere like Barcelona all you want is a good base as you go out and eat in the city and you're out all day seeing the sights, and this hotel is just that.Although I still prefer my 4/5 star luxury hotels, if I'm staying in Barcelona again I will definately book here next time, and would def look at lower rated hotels when going on other city breaks! 
