<Content>The perfect hub Although I enjoy being pampered by four or five star facilities, there are cases when there should be a trade-off between certain things. Hotel Cortes is the (only and) best 2-star hotel I have ever stayed at. Located in a small pedestrian street leading to Las Ramblas, it is within easy reach of some of the most exciting sights of Barcelona. ( 2mins to the Ramblas and the underground station, 3 mins to the Catalan Square, 5 mins to the Cathedral, 10 mins to the Music palace. The airport bus drops you off at the Catalan Square.) I had a single room on the 4th floor which was tiny but unbelievably clean. The room had the basics only, do not expect a minibar in a two star facility. The TV and the fresh daily towels were a pleasant surprise as was the AC and the hairdryer. Reception staff were extremely kind and helpful. It might have been the length of my stay (8 days) combined with the friendliness of the staff that it was like going home when I returned to my hotel in the evening. There is a health-food restaurant right next to the hotel which is perfect for solitary female travellers but the restaurant opposite was also OK. The only thing I did not like about the hotel was breakfast. The breakfast room was in an adjoining restaurant, you had to go through a smoky bar to get your continental breakfast not earlier than 8. My room overlooked the courtyard and was very quiet. I do not think there could have been a more conveniently located hotel for 鈧?0 per night in Barcelona. 
